Package org.eclipse.mosaic.rti.api

Class AbstractFederateAmbassador

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.rti.api.AbstractFederateAmbassador
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<FederateAmbassador>, FederateAmbassador
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractNetworkAmbassador, AbstractSumoAmbassador, ApplicationAmbassador, CellAmbassador, EnvironmentAmbassador, MappingAmbassador, OutputAmbassador, SnsAmbassador
public abstract class AbstractFederateAmbassador extends Object implements FederateAmbassador
Provides basic function of a federate ambassador and declares abstract methods to be implemented.

  • Method Details

    • processInteraction

      protected void processInteraction(Interaction interaction) throws InternalFederateException
      This method is called by the AbstractFederateAmbassadors whenever the federate can safely process interactions in its incoming interaction queue. The decision when it is safe to process such an interaction depends on the policies TimeRegulating and TimeConstrained that has to be set by the federate.
      Parameters:
      interaction - the interaction to be processed
      Throws:
      InternalFederateException - an exception inside of a joined federate occurs

    • processTimeAdvanceGrant

      protected void processTimeAdvanceGrant(long time) throws InternalFederateException
      This method is called by the AbstractFederateAmbassador when a time advance has been granted by the RTI. Before this call is placed, any unprocessed interaction is forwarded to the federate using the processInteraction method.
      Parameters:
      time - The timestamp towards which the federate can advance it local time.
      Throws:
      InternalFederateException

    • advanceTime

      public final void advanceTime(long time) throws InternalFederateException
      This method is called by the time management service. If the ambassador has requested to advance its internal clock, the time management service calls this method to signal that a time advance request is granted.
      Specified by:
      advanceTime in interface FederateAmbassador
      Parameters:
      time - Time in nano seconds until this federate is allowed to advance its internal clock.
      Throws:
      InternalFederateException - an exception inside of a joined federate occurs

    • receiveInteraction

      public final void receiveInteraction(@Nonnull Interaction interaction) throws InternalFederateException
      The receiveInteraction method is called by the time management service when an interaction is available for which this federate is registered. If the receiver wants to advance its internal clock based on the interaction it has to request a time advance. The receiver is not allowed to advance its internal clock without granted request.
      Specified by:
      receiveInteraction in interface FederateAmbassador
      Parameters:
      interaction - An object extending the interaction object and containing shared data by another federate.
      Throws:
      InternalFederateException - an exception if error while receiving interaction

    • setRtiAmbassador

      public final void setRtiAmbassador(@Nonnull RtiAmbassador rti)
      Description copied from interface: FederateAmbassador
      Assigns a new RtiAmbassador to this federate. The RtiAmbassador is the bridge the the RTI providing various methods, e.g. to exchange interactions. Each ambassador requires its own instance of the RtiAmbassador.
      Specified by:
      setRtiAmbassador in interface FederateAmbassador
      Parameters:
      rti - a RtiAmbassador instance

    • createFederateExecutor

      @Nonnull public FederateExecutor createFederateExecutor(String host, int port, CLocalHost.OperatingSystem os)
      If a federate should be started by MOSAIC, an implementation of FederateExecutor must be provided. This method must return a nonnull object. The default implementation returns a NopFederateExecutor, which does nothing when called.
      Specified by:
      createFederateExecutor in interface FederateAmbassador
      Parameters:
      host - name of the host (as specified in /etc/hosts.xml)
      port - port number to be used by this federate
      os - operating system enum
      Returns:
      the FederateExecutor which starts the federate
